data.title: Takin' a Risk, Tryin' Again [Archive]
data.meta_description:
1. Every thread touching this subject has run on for awhile, then been closed when it veered into politics. SO: THIS IS NOT ABOUT THE "GIBSON RAID," AND I DON'T WANT TO TALK ABOUT THAT.  AT ALL.  No pundit clips, no debate.  Nada. 
 
2. The Lacey Act is more than a century old (signed by Pres. McKinley, didja know that?), but its recent (2008) amendments have made it relevant to mandolin builders and owners.  Certain "plant products" are now restricted from import and export, including woods
data.text: View Full Version : Lacey Act - Takin' a Risk, Tryin' Again
